  "notes": "v3.3 + per-document Evidence Evaluator agent that emits a structured DocTrust report (internal_consistency, encyclopedic_quality, specificity, relevance, composite trust_score, closed-enum red_flags). The trust_score lands in a new reliability slot (W_TRUST=0.35, formula: 0.40·retrieval + 0.25·confidence + 0.35·trust − 0.10·minority), and red_flags are surfaced to the Skeptic. Hypothesis: a structured per-doc evidence-quality signal should sharpen reliability ordering and let the Skeptic prune misinfo more aggressively without over-pruning legitimate variants. Result: REGRESSION across the board — EM −0.042, F1 −0.025, Misinfo-rejection −0.042 — at +81% LLM calls and +71% latency. The Evaluator adds noise to reliability (gpt-4o-mini is not stable at small-text quality rating with bounded floats) and shifts the Skeptic's decision boundary in the wrong direction (the new red_flags overlap with legitimate short answers in the pure_correct category). v4.0 is published as a frozen NEGATIVE result and is NOT a Pareto improvement over v3. v3.3_analyzer_tuned remains the recommended default."
